  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Load `Boxes` from a database.  Since there is only one scope,\n",
    "we could just call the method with no arguments and it will figure\n",
    "out what we want, but in this demo we'll load a specific named scope."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "boxes = db.read_boxes('GBNRTC')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "`Box` definitions."

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},

  {

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "ChainedBox: Automated Vehicles\n",
       "   ●             Land Use - CBD Focus >= 1\n",
       "   ●                 Freeway Capacity >= 1.25\n",
       "   ●            Auto IVTT Sensitivity <= 0.9\n",
       "   ◌               Peak Transit Share\n",
       "   ◌           AM Trip Length (miles)\n",
       "   ◌              Total LRT Boardings\n",
       "   ◌    Corridor Kensington Daily VMT\n",
       "   ◌  Downtown to Airport Travel Time\n",
       "   ◌          Total Transit Boardings\n",
       "   ◌           AM Trip Time (minutes)\n",
       "   ◌                  Region-wide VMT"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "chain = boxes.get_chain('Automated Vehicles')\n",
    "chain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's load some data from the database.  We'll use 'lhs_2', which has\n",
    "a large latin hypercube sample of metamodel results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_from_database(\n",
    "        db,\n",
    "        scope,\n",
    "        design_name,\n",
    "        feature_names,\n",
    "):\n",
    "    X = db.read_experiment_all(scope.name, design_name)\n",
    "    # Put feature names in order\n",
    "    m_names = [i for i in feature_names if i in scope.get_measure_names()]\n",
    "    x_names = [i for i in feature_names if i in scope.get_uncertainty_names()]\n",
    "    l_names = [i for i in feature_names if i in scope.get_lever_names()]\n",
    "    return X.loc[:, x_names+l_names+m_names]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df = load_from_database(\n",
    "    db,\n",
    "    scope,\n",
    "    feature_names=chain.relevant_features|chain.demanded_features,\n",
    "    design_name='lhs_2',\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `inside` method of `Box` and `ChainedBox` (added in TMIP-EMAT v0.1.4) is shown below. \n",
    "It is a quick and easy way to filter all the experiments in a DataFrame that are inside (or outside) the box."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def inside(box, df):\n",
    "    within = pandas.Series(True, index=df.index)\n",
    "    for label, bounds in box.thresholds.items():\n",
    "        if bounds.lowerbound is not None:\n",
    "            within &= (df[label] >= bounds.lowerbound)\n",
    "        if bounds.upperbound is not None:\n",
    "            within &= (df[label] <= bounds.upperbound)\n",
    "    return within\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Monkey-patch for prior versions\n",
    "emat.Box.inside = inside\n",
    "emat.ChainedBox.inside = inside"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['in_box'] = in_box = chain.inside(df)"
   ]
  },
  {
